args: In one of her imaginary worlds, Mym found\nherself faced with a dilemma:
Did she want a human heart,\nor just a human body?
All good, Mym? Ya look pale.
Well, I suppose I didn't sleep all\nthat well last night.
Ya need rest. Let's find a town.
You're the only friend what I got.\nIt's the least I can do.
(He might not be the same person\nI'm used to, but he's just as kind.)
(I want to do something for him.\nI NEED to do something.)
(I don't have my dragon power anymore;\nI'm just a human with no real redeeming\nfeatures to speak of.)
Don't do anything reckless like last time!\nYa hear me?!
(I might have the heart of a dragon,\nbut my body is still very human.\nI must be careful!)
Whew! That was close. Now take THIS!
I think that's the last of them.
(These fiends would give a dragon no\ntrouble, but I can barely defend myself!)
Good. Now let's see, which way was the\nnearest town...
Allow me! It'll be easy to tell from up\nin the airâ€”wait. Ugh!
What're you on about?\nJust wait, I'll check the map.
(Well, I'm CERTAINLY going to be terrible\nat this. I've barely even looked at a map\nbefore, much less navigated with one.)
Okay, I got it. Let's go.
(I can't help him in battle OR adventuring.)
(What reason even is there for me\nto be at his side?)
Well, we're still on the road,\nbut the sun is going down.
(Too bad all we have is this tough,\ntasteless dried meat.)
(I fear I've become quite used to Cleo\nmaking fancy dishes on our travels.)
Er, but hypothetically, if I was able to\ncook, would that make you happy?
Yeah, I guess I wouldn't really care\none way or the other.
You don't want to eat better food\nthan dried meat?!
'Course I do. But cookin' ain't\nwhat I want from you.
And what exactly DO you want from me?!
Guess I just want ya at my side, is all.
Just havin' ya there calms me.
This is a tough old world, and sometimes\nit's hard to trudge through it.
But when you're with me, I'm happy.
I only really belong here when I'm\nwith you, Mym. I only... That's when...
Well, I suppose he looks a little more\nat peace now? That's something.
He said he only feels like he belongs\nhere when he is with me.
It seems I am the only pillar of\nemotional support he has.
Which means that so long as I am being\nindecisive, he will never be at rest.
I will become human in body AND heart!\nI will forsake the life of a dragon!
And as a human, I will do all I can\nto support my beloved!
I'll learn to cook! I'll learn to read maps!\nI'll learn how to make these little stick\narms better able to wield a weapon!
I will lay down all that I am in order to\nsee this relationship made whole!
